  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Food addiction (FA) is a behavioral addiction characterized by a high consumption of
      palatable foods, which markedly activate the reward system, despite adverse consequences. FA
      was first described in 1956 but remains controversial. The Yale Food Addiction Scale (YFAS),
      developed by Gearhardt et al. in 2009, is currently regarded as the &quot;Gold Standard&quot; for FA
      screening. In a previous study, we established a Food Addiction Screening Test using
      artificial intelligence. The main objective of the present study is to validate the
      sensitivity, specificity and precision for FA diagnosis in a sample of patient suffering from
      obesity and healthy volunteers.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
